comment.author: 42775333@N02
comment._content: Aircraft in photo is a Hawker Sea Hawk F Mk.I WF144 being flown by Sqdn. Ldr. Neville Duke, a famous Hawker Test Pilot.  This aircraft was the second production aircraft from the initial Hawker production batch of 35 aircraft.  First flying on February 21, 1952, it along with WF145 were used for carrier trials aboard HMS Eagle, eventually seeing service with the first Sea Hawk squadron, No. 806 (Ace of Diamonds) on HMS Eagle & HMS Albion.
